Unwanted maneuver or stop by vehicle - the vehicle's trajectory planner produced a trajectory that was unsatisfactory, or the vehicle's control systems failed to follow a planned trajectory with sufficient accuracy

Localization/position discrepancy - a problem was observed in the vehicle's estimate of its position; causes may include the accuracy of the imu, lidar, and gps sensor data, the algorithms used to process that data, or the accuracy of the vehicle's maps

Perception discrepancy - a discrepancy arose between how vehicle's perception sensor (radar, lidar, and camera) data perceived the vehicle's environment, and how a human driver perceived the environment

Software/Hardware problem - a vehicle software or hardware system stopped operating normally; includes issues related to computing/sensing hardware, vehicle actuation hardware, operating system software, and intra-vehicle communication software
